The ANC has disbanded the Western Cape Provincial Executive Committee. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC has disbanded the Western Cape Provincial Executive Committee (PEC). This follows the meeting of the party's National Executive Committee (NEC) which took place on 26-29 July at St Georges Hotel in Tshwane. WATCH: ANC details NEC decisions after Irene meeting The party says it's concerned about the "growing internal disintegration that turn to play itself out in the public, making it difficult for the PEC to exercise its duties". According to the ANC NEC, a provincial interim committee will be established to work towards aÂ provincial conference. 